Residents of Lokoja have commended GOtv for its local and international content programming. GOtv officially launched its services in Lokoja on June 4, 2022, making Lokoja the 46th city with GOtv network coverage in Nigeria. GOtv services are currently available in 25 states across the country. Some residents who spoke on the quality of local content delivery said GOtv’s Africa Magic channels has been an instant hit in their households.   Rumour of dating popular footballer causing me problems…     Dbanj congratulates N1million birthday giveaway winner     D’Banj celebrates 42nd birthday in grand style   Dangali, a civil servant, said “in the last few days, GOtv has made it possible for this family to spend more and more time together, and Africa Magic Hausa has become a favourite in his home due to its direct connection to our cultural roots.” A youth corp member, Onome, said she bought the GOtv package during the launch and it has been less homesick since then “One thing I miss is hearing my native language. I bought GOtv during the launch when I heard that one of the stations shows Igbo programmes on Africa Magic Igbo. I enjoy exceptional entertainment in Igbo. It helps me feel at home,” she said. Gotv offers over 80 exciting channels covering news, music, sports, documentaries, series, movies, and children’s programmes, which are carefully selected to cater to a variety of different tastes and family viewing needs at a very affordable price.